{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d80418ab-5d93-41cb-bd20-a7c98c2b10d6","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit sets `Skip` as a **property on the test attribute** itself, unlike the others which use a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cfd96a11-e86d-448c-8cb7-75ca3b8b7bd4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without tools.","outputTokens":302,"requestId":"CFDC:131578:14D4325:1818F65:69EC136D"},"id":"c4e60784-39d2-4de0-b088-2b5e4003c7c9","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:05:56.251Z","parentId":"d8f79ee4-929d-4300-a8e3-446c3bee9db8"}
